"{\"abstract\":\"Classical clustering methods usually face tough challenges when we have a larger set of features compared to the number of items to be partitioned. We propose a Sparse MinMax k-Means Clustering approach by reformulating the objective of the MinMax k-Means algorithm (a variation of classical kMeans that minimizes the maximum intra-cluster variance instead of the sum of intra-cluster variances), into a new weighted between-cluster sum of squares (BCSS) form. We impose sparse regularization on these weights to make it suitable for high-dimensional clustering. We seek to use the advantages of the MinMax k-Means algorithm in the high-dimensional space to generate good quality clusters. The efficacy of the proposal is showcased through comparison against a few representative clustering methods over several real world datasets.\",\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"46669181\",\"name\":\"Sayak Dey\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/46669181\"},{\"authorId\":\"1747655\",\"name\":\"Swagatam Das\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1747655\"},{\"authorId\":\"1768588\",\"name\":\"R. Mallipeddi\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/author/1768588\"}],\"citationVelocity\":0,\"citations\":[],\"corpusId\":220484654,\"doi\":\"10.24963/ijcai.2020/291\",\"fieldsOfStudy\":[\"Computer Science\"],\"influentialCitationCount\":0,\"is_open_access\":false,\"is_publisher_licensed\":false,\"paperId\":\"9b29bbe3a2053f51e5989d9a8409180fbd9f73da\",\"references\":[{\"arxivId\":null,\"authors\":[{\"authorId\":\"70048667\",\"name\":\"J. M. Pe\\u00f1a\"},{\"authorId\":\"144762651\",\"name\":\"J. Lozano\"},{\"authorId\":\"144999310\",\"name\":\"P. Larra\\u00f1aga\"}],\"doi\":\"10.1016/S0167-8655(99)00069-0\",\"intent\":[],\"isInfluential\":false,\"paperId\":\"3930e2c2d888a800ec405cedf43bc014287dc1a3\",\"title\":\"An empirical comparison of four initialization methods for the K-Means algorithm\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/pap